---
description: Backend API security rules
globs:
  - src/app/api/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: true
---

# Backend Security

- Never expose NMI, Supabase service role keys, or any secret keys
  to the client.
- Every protected API route must verify the Supabase session.
- Sensitive data must never appear in logs. Never log:
  SSN, credit card numbers, authentication tokens, passwords.
- All API routes must return consistent error responses:
  { error: string, code: string }
- Sensitive routes must be rate-limited: signup, login, KYC submission.
- Validate all input before processing. Never trust client data.
